article.headline: Bucknell 87, West Alabama 50
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Bryson Johnson scored 27 points on a career-high nine 3-pointers and Bucknell set a school record with 17 treys in an 87-50 rout of West Alabama on Saturday. All 15 of Johnson's attempts were beyond the arc in the TicketCity Legends Classic subregional game. Cameron Ayers added 20 points on 4 of 5 from long range as the Bison (4-2) attempted 34 3-pointers, tying a school mark, to finish at 50 percent. Bucknell, which led 48-25 at halftime, has won four straight games. The Bison were 30 of 59 (50.8 percent) from the field compared to 17 of 62 (27.4 percent) for the NCAA Division II Tigers (1-5). Bucknell had hit 15 3-pointers twice before, at Villanova in 2007-08 and at Boston College last season. Phillip Morris led West Alabama with 11 points on 4 of 5 shooting. The Bison had a 46-33 rebounding edge and dished out 23 assists.
